images.name: Lamar Jackson waltzes in for a Ravens score
images.caption: Lamar Jackson keeps it himself and maneuvers in for an 10-yard touchdown for the Ravens.

articles.description: — Josh Allen led Buffalo to three scores in the final four minutes, the last a 32-yard field goal by Matt Prater as time expired, and the Bills rallied from 15 points down to stun the Baltimore Ravens 41-40 in a season-opening Sunday night thriller.
articles.headline: Josh Allen rallies Bills from 15-point deficit in 41-40 season-opening thriller over Ravens

images.name: 250907 Parsons [1296x729]
images.caption: Micah Parsons reached a top speed of 18.47 mph when he chased down Lions QB Jared Goff, according to NFL Next Gen Stats. That was his fastest max speed on any of his 53.5 career sacks.
images.credit: Tork Mason-USA TODAY Network via Imagn Images

images.name: Micah Parsons gets his first sack as a Packer
images.caption: Micah Parsons chases down Jared Goff for his first sack as a Green Bay Packer.

articles.description: Less than two weeks after being traded to Green Bay, Micah Parson got his first sack and was second on the team with three pressures during Sunday's win versus Detroit.
articles.headline: Micah Parsons quickly makes impact in his Packers debut

articles.description: The NFL regular-season debut for No. 1 pick Cam Ward, who completed 12 of 28 passes for 112 yards, had its share of rough moments as the Tennessee Titans lost a 20-12 decision to the Denver Broncos on Sunday at Empower Field at Mile High.
articles.headline: Tennessee Titans fall to Denver Broncos in Cam Ward's debut
